# UI & Styling Rules

## Core Principle

- NEVER write custom CSS unless absolutely necessary
- ALWAYS use Tailwind CSS utilities

## Tailwind

- Use design tokens (spacing, colors, typography)
- Avoid arbitrary values (e.g., px)
- Use consistent spacing scale

## shadcn/ui

- Use shadcn components as base building blocks
- Extend components instead of rewriting UI
- Keep styling consistent with shadcn defaults

## Layout

- Use Flexbox and Grid
- Maintain consistent padding and spacing
- Ensure responsiveness (mobile-first)

## Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML
- Ensure keyboard navigation
- Add aria attributes when needed